How efficiently this model can perform in real scenarios? We answer this question by projecting the expected COVID-19 cases in Estonia and Rhône-Alpes region in France using the fully mixed model and compared the results with the real cases (Sects. 4.2.3 and 4.2.4).The limitation of traditional compartmental epidemiological models is that they do not account for the role of reducing social connectivity (or isolation) and mobility restrictions during the outbreak of a pandemic such as COVID-19. The proposed model overcomes this constraint. We discovered that the reproduction number \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
