				\begin{document}$$R_0$$\end{document}R0 for a pandemic is influenced by social connectivity and mobility. We also discovered that restricting movement during a pandemic decreases the fraction of individuals in an infected compartment, and restricting social interaction (or isolation) slows the peak and reduces the number of infected individuals from the pandemic. We believe that these models can help to adopt a balanced strategy to address a pandemic crisis.

