What are the outcomes of restricting the mobility (for top-X percentile) of strongly connected locations in a complex network?

We perform various simulation experiments to explain the proposed model for complex network on ConNet by selecting the seed infection location randomly. It is to be noted that the model will behave as a standard SIR model in two cases, (i) if \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
